        <exercise xml:id="SAR-intro-exp-areamodel">
          <title>The Area Model for Multiplication</title>
            <statement>
              <p> 
                This problem illustrates the Area Model for Multiplication, an 
                effective way of helping elementary school students visualize the operation 
                of multiplication. <idx><h>area model for multiplication</h></idx>
                <ol>
                  <li>
                    <p>
                      On graph paper sketch a <m>3 \times 5</m> rectangle.  Show the fifteen 
                      squares that make up the area.
                    </p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <p>
                      Note that 12 can be factored as <m>1 \times 12</m>, <m>2 \times 6</m>, 
                      or <m>3 \times 4</m>.  Sketch area models for each of these products.
                    </p>
                  </li>
                </ol>
