        <exercise xml:id="ExtConc-intro-exp-areamodel-twodigit">
          <title>Area Model for Two-digit Numbers</title>
          <introduction>
            <p>
              Multiplication of two-digit numbers can be represented 
              using the area model: for example, to multiply 47 by 25 we can represent 
              47 as 4 tens and 7 ones and 25 as 2 tens and 5 ones.  We then can sketch 
              the product as shown in <xref ref="fig-hw2digit-rectangle"/>.  
            </p>
          </introduction>
            <task>
              <statement>
                <p>
                  Determine the area of each of the four subrectangles pictured. Here, the squares 
                  on the grid are not <m>1\times 1</m> but defined by the notations on the sides.
                </p>
              </statement>
              <hint>
                <p>
                  One of the subrectangles is a <m>5\times 40</m>-rectangle. What are 
                  the others? 
                </p>
              </hint>
            </task>
            <task>
              <statement>
                <p>
                  Add the four areas of the subrectangles together to find the total area.
                </p>
              </statement>
            </task>
            <task>
                <statement>
                <p>
                  The standard algorithm to multiply  <m>47 \times 25</m> is shown
                  in <xref ref="fig-twodigitalgorithm"/>.   
                  Identify what the 235 and 940 in the algorithm represent in the area 
                  model pictured at the beginning of this exercise.
                </p>
                </statement>
                <hint>
                  <p>
                    Consider sums of areas.
                  </p>
                </hint>
              </task>
                <figure xml:id="fig-hw2digit-areamodel">
                  <caption>A rectangular model and algorithm for two-digit multiplication</caption>
                <sidebyside widths="60% 30%">
                  <figure xml:id="fig-hw2digit-rectangle">
                    <caption>Rectangular Model</caption>
                  <image component="web" source="hw2digit-areamodel.svg" width="40%">
                    <shortdescription>
                      A rectangle labeled with sides 40+7 and 20+5 and split into 
                      subrectangles 40 by 20, 40 by 5, 7 by 20, and 7 by 5.
                    </shortdescription>
                  </image>
                  <image component="print" source="hw2digit-areamodel.png" width="40%">
                    <shortdescription>
                      A rectangle labeled with sides 40+7 and 20+5 and split into 
                      subrectangles 40 by 20, 40 by 5, 7 by 20, and 7 by 5.
                    </shortdescription>
                  </image>
                </figure>
                <figure xml:id="fig-twodigitalgorithm">
                  <caption>Algorithm</caption>
                  <tabular halign="right">
                    <row header="no" bottom="none">
                      <cell>47</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row header="no" bottom="medium">
                      <cell><m>\times</m> 25</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row header="no" bottom="none">
                      <cell>235</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row header="no" bottom="minor">
                      <cell>+ 940</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row header="no" bottom="none">
                      <cell>1175</cell>
                    </row>
                  </tabular>
                </figure>
                </sidebyside>
                </figure>
              
            </exercise>
              
